WEBVTT

00:02.883 --> 00:07.359
The first teenage comic book crime-fighter not to be under the wing of an older superhero,...

00:07.756 --> 00:11.905
...Spider-Man had to learn for himself that with great power came great responsibility.

00:12.325 --> 00:15.137
Welcome to Watchmojo.com. I'm your host Derek Allen...

00:15.467 --> 00:19.067
...and today, we'll be exploring why Peter Parker became Spider-Man.

00:19.365 --> 00:24.765
To avoid confusion, it should be noted that we're following the storyline which unfolded in the comic book.

00:25.066 --> 00:27.969
Members of the government intelligence agency, S.H.I.E.L.D.,...

00:28.136 --> 00:31.232
...Peter Parker's parents were killed while he was still an infant.

00:31.334 --> 00:35.714
Adopted by his Aunt May and Uncle Ben, Peter grew up fascinated with science;...

00:35.844 --> 00:39.155
...however, also he was timid and unpopular among his friends.

00:39.329 --> 00:44.737
While at a science exhibition, Peter was bitten by a radioactive spider, and shortly after discovers...

00:44.850 --> 00:51.207
...he has been given a set of spider-like powers such as superhuman strength, agility, and the ability to crawl on walls,...

00:51.418 --> 00:55.687
...as well as a strong sixth sense, usually described as his spider sense.

00:55.907 --> 01:01.197
Peter Parker's initial reaction to these newly acquired powers is to use them for fame and fortune.

01:01.401 --> 01:03.788
However, one night during the television special,...

01:03.929 --> 01:07.995
...Peter allows a thief to escape the TV station, claiming it was not his problem.

01:08.209 --> 01:11.267
The same thief goes on to kill Peter's uncle in a mugging.

01:11.538 --> 01:16.929
The guilt from knowing he could have prevented his uncle's death leads Peter to turn to a life of crime fighting...

01:17.047 --> 01:19.891
...and is arguably the main basis for his moral core.

